x \to 1
\frac 1{1-x} \to \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} 1 = \infty
f
f
[0,1[
f
 \frac 1{1-x} = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} x^n, 
 \int_0^1 \frac 1{1-x} \, dx = \int_0^1 \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} x^n \, dx = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \int_0^1 x^n \, dx = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac 1{n+1} = \infty. 
1-x = u
\frac 1u
 \int_0^1 \frac 1{1-x} dx = \lim_{a \nearrow 1} \int_0^a \frac 1{1-x} dx = \lim_{a \nearrow 1} -\log(1-a) = \infty. 
 \int_0^1 \frac 1{1-x} dx = \int_0^1 \frac 1u du. 
 = \lim_{a \searrow 0} \int_a^1 \frac 1u du = \lim_{a \searrow 0} [\log(1) - \log(a)] = \infty. 
